{"author":{"id":"977fec8a59c245f25e0e700fa290ef50836c624572869487e9e47fedc85061ee"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1506968410,"nonce":"4XomdDOno6PycpsMDm9Kst/U/eY=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMzMzYyMDUxMw==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/1501#issuecomment-333620513"},"message":"\u003e Visually, if I have dataset collection [a, b, c, d, e, f, g] and control file [H], I get the results of callpeak(a, H) and nothing else.\n\nThat is not exactly right, a,b,c,d,e,f,g will be treated as replicates, and the first item here determines the output name. Making the tool inputs conditionally non-multiple makes sense at the moment, but Ideally it would be better if it was easier to create nested dataset collections. In this case you would make your deepest nesting level the replicates, so that the level (from flat to deep) are Sample/Replicate, where each is one collection. That should work for the tool as it is now (except we don't have a User Interface for this now).","files":null}]}